President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. Christopher Schroeder was nominated for Assistant Attorney General for the Office of Legal Policy at the Department of Justice. Paul Anastas was nominated for Assistant Administrator for Office of Research and Development at the Environmental Protection Agency. Sherry Glied was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Planning and Evaluation at the Department of Health and Human Services. Winslow Sargeant was nominated for Chief Counsel for Advocacy at the Small Business Administration. Ambassador Nancy Powell was nominated for Director General of the Foreign Service at the Department of State. Deborah Matz was nominated for Chair of the National Credit Union Administration. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Max Cleland as Secretary of the American Battle Monuments Commission.